Reasoning: The paper deals with the implementation of a MAC layer in the SINR wireless network model, which is a topic related to network protocols and communication. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also involves algorithms and computational complexity, which suggests categories such as cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The use of information theory concepts and the analysis of local parameters in the algorithm design may also relate to cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.SY (Systems and Control).
